Module qilletni.api
Package dev.qilletni.api.music

Interface MusicTypeConverter

public interface MusicTypeConverter
Converts music types from one service provider to another. Often times, a conversion is not possible. Examples of this include a playlist that is only available on Spotify, or an album that is only available on Last.fm. The most important example of this is typically converting a track from one service provider to another, to allow, for instance, playing tracks from Last.Fm on Spotify.

Multiple types may be given to each method, one for every service provider that the type is available on currently. There will always be at least one in the list, so List.getFirst() may be used.
